  "body": "Currently it's possible to run Besu on an incomplete fast-synced db with full sync enabled. This causes the node to stall out.\n\nSteps to reproduce:\n * Start Besu in fast sync mode, and wait for some chain data to be downloaded\n\n * Stop Besu\n\n * Start Besu in full sync mode\n\n * Observe that Besu will disconnect all new peers and log a world state unavailable error:\n\n   * `2019-09-18 18:12:50.214-04:00 | nioEventLoopGroup-3-1 | WARN | FullSyncTargetManager | Disconnecting 0xeb1241b5b761b7853f... because world state is not available at common ancestor at block 13663 `\n\nProbability: Remote\nSeverity: Critical\n\n![Screenshot (103).png](https://images.zenhubusercontent.com/56afc50a6caf56c9d38c2113/bc84ae5e-1b66-4626-97e1-e44cd071291f)\n![Screenshot (105).png](https://images.zenhubusercontent.com/56afc50a6caf56c9d38c2113/adf9b8af-bb4c-4107-86f4-da59fef92052)",
